> This is true.  By federal law, if you don't protect your trademark you lose
> it, so your issue is really with the legislature, not VW.
> In my recent foray into Fiat land (having traded a used Bus engine for a '76
> Spider convertible - boy is that car fun to drive!), I learned that VW is
> not alone in their diligence.  Recently Fiat forced a parts specialist in
> the U.S. to remove the word "Fiat" from their business name on the grounds
> of trademark infringement - this despite the fact that Fiat pulled out of
> the U.S. market for 17 years ago!!  I suppose they want to keep that
> trademark safe just in case there is a sudden groundswell of demand in the
> U.S. for notoriously unreliable Italain motor vehicles. :-)
